To start and check tomcat running process

✅ If you mean: "Can I still use terminal while Tomcat is running?"

sudo -u tomcat /opt/tomcat/bin/startup.sh

It runs in the background.

You can still:
	• Run commands
	• Edit files
	• SSH normally
	• Install packages
To confirm it's running:
ss -tulpn | grep 8080
or
ps aux | grep tomcat

✅ If you mean: "How do I monitor Tomcat while it's running?"

You can watch logs live:
tail -f /opt/tomcat/logs/catalina.out

That shows real-time activity.
Press:
CTRL + C
to stop watching.
